{
  "text": "Validity of this system model can be fortified when the packet is transmitted in a narrowband channel or approximately static environments. In fact, when the packet transmission time T p is smaller than the channel coherence time T c (T c T p ), channel can be readily assumed to be a constant. For example, when the carrier frequency f c = 1.8 GHz and the mobile speed is \u03bd = 10 km/h, then T c \u2248 11 ms is much larger than the duration of one LTE OFDM symbol (\u2248 0.07 ms) [CITATION_1] , which justifies the validity of this approximation.",
